flashcard.question:
\mathbf{Classical\ inequality\ I:\ }
            Let $a, b \geq 0$, and $p \geq 1$. Prove that
            $$(a+b)^p \leq 2^{p-1} (a^p + b^p).$$

\textbf{Holder's\ inequality:\ }

            Let $p,q \geq 1$ be conjugate exponents. Let $$x=\{x_{i}\}_{1}^{\infty}\in l^{p}$$ and $$y=\{y_{i}\}_{1}^{\infty}\in l^{q}$$. Then $$xy=\{x_{i}y_{i}\}_{1}^{\infty} \in l^{1}$$ and $$\sum_{1}^{\infty}{|x_{i}y_{i}|}\leq
            \left(\sum_{1}^{\infty}{|x_{i}|^{p}}\right)^{\frac{1}{p}}
            \cdot
            \left(\sum_{1}^{\infty}{|y_{i}|^{q}}\right)^{\frac{1}{q}}.$$
